OL,3,CWhy is the South West building so many
OL,4,Cnew homes when thousands are empty?
OL,6,F"It only becomes illegal when it
OL,7,Fstarts to have a detrimental impact on
OL,8,Fother properties. We have to build a
OL,9,Freally clear case for enforcement;
OL,10,Fit's really labour-intensive. It can
OL,11,Foften cost a lot of money to bring
OL,12,Fcases to court."
OL,14,FWith limited powers, it took the
OL,15,Fcouncil more than a decade of legal
OL,16,Fwrangling to force the Oldfield Park
OL,17,Fowner to sell. And B&NES is one of the
OL,18,Fminority of councils with a dedicated
OL,19,FEmpty Property Officer. Two thirds of
OL,20,Fcouncils don't have anyone tasked with
OL,21,Ffighting these empty property battles.
